Communicated by:
ProMED

[Japanese encephalitis (JE) transmission continues to gradually affect more people and pigs but incidence may be slowing. The above report indicates that JE virus infection in pig production is economically serious with affected piggeries experiencing losses of up to 60-80%.

The integrated human and animal health response by the Australian government is commendable as a good example of a One Health approach to an emerging disease outbreak. Ongoing vaccination of people who are in areas of higher JE risk, particularly near affected piggeries where JE virus is being transmitted, is not mentioned above but is another active preventive response to the outbreak. - Mod.TY

